
Overview of noun revelation

The noun revelation has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (4) disclosure, revelation, revealing -- (the speech act of making something evident)
2. (4) revelation -- (an enlightening or astonishing disclosure)
3. revelation, divine revelation -- (communication of knowledge to man by a divine or supernatural agency)
4. Revelation, Revelation of Saint John the Divine, Apocalypse, Book of Revelation -- (the last book of the New Testament; contains visionary descriptions of heaven and of conflicts between good and evil and of the end of the world; attributed to Saint John the Apostle)
